<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <style>

    .box{ width: 50px; height: 50px; }
    
    .ex-1 .parent-div{ background: #bbb; border: 2px solid black; width: 400px; }
    .ex-1 .child-div-1{ background: yellow; }
    .ex-1 .child-div-2{ background: red; position: fixed; bottom: 50px; right: 50px;}
    .ex-1 .child-div-3{ background: blue; }
    .ex-1 .child-div-4{ background: gray; }
  
    .ex-2 .parent-div{ background: #bbb; border: 2px solid black; width: 400px; }
    .ex-2 .child-span-1{ background: yellow; }
    .ex-2 .child-span-2{ background: red; position: fixed; bottom: 50px; right: 150px;}
    .ex-2 .child-span-3{ background: blue; }
    .ex-2 .child-span-4{ background: gray; }

  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <p>When the position is set to absolute, the element is removed from the document flow.</p>
  <p>This element will placed exactly with top/right/bottom/left based on browser window.</p>

  <div class="ex-1">
    <h4>ex-1</h4>
    <div class="parent-div">
      <div class="child-div-1 box"></div>
      <div class="child-div-2 box"></div>
      <div class="child-div-3 box"></div>
      <div class="child-div-4 box"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="ex-2">
    <h4>ex-2</h4>
    <p>The fixed element will be removed from document flow, then the display of the element will be changed</p>
    <div class="parent-div">
      <span class="child-span-1 box">span-1</span>
      <span class="child-span-2 box">span-2</span>
      <span class="child-span-3 box">span-3</span>
      <span class="child-span-4 box">span-4</span>
    </div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
